properties.areaDesc: Lake Superior West of Line from Manitou Island to Marquette MI Beyond 5NM from shore; Lake Superior East of a line from Manitou Island to Marquette MI and West of a line from Grand Marais MI to the US/Canadian Border Beyond 5NM from shore; Lake Superior from Grand Marais MI to Whitefish Point MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian border
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 10 at 10:37AM EST until January 12 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt and
waves 7 to 10 feet possible.

* WHERE...Lake Superior from Grand Marais MI to Whitefish Point
MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian border, Lake Superior East
of a line from Manitou Island to Marquette MI and West of a
line from Grand Marais MI to the US/Canadian Border Beyond 5NM
from shore and Lake Superior West of Line from Manitou Island
to Marquette MI Beyond 5NM from shore.

* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through Sunday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING
